s theory, infinitely many\nsolutions are obtained when $M$ is a special function and $\\lambda$ is small\nenough. We note that our paper covers a novel feature of Kirchhoff problems,\nthat is, the Kirchhoff function $M(0)=0$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Jun 2019 07:02:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-20"}
